        "subtopic": "Combined Work",
        "content": "If A can do a job in x days and B can do it in y days, then:\n(A + B)’s 1-day work = 1/x + 1/y\n\n**Example:** A can do work in 6 days, B in 3 days. Together they finish 1/6 + 1/3 = 1/2 of work per day. So, total time = 2 days."
